  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently in active selling mode as SPX sits just below the 6575 flip strike in a strong PIN regime, with the massive 32.4B gamma wall at 6580 acting as a hard ceiling where selling pressure intensifies. The recent GEX surge combined with spot trading 12 points below the flip indicates dealers are providing liquidity by selling into any rallies toward 6575-6580, creating strong mean-reverting conditions. Watch for dealer buying support to emerge if price tests the 6550 negative gamma zone, but expect continued chop and rejection at the 6575-6580 resistance cluster as long as we remain in this high-gamma PIN environment.",
